    <h1>Managing contacts</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Note about the "Managing contacts" page of the manual</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This page of the manual describes all settings that are available in the <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong> menu in the terra back end via the central login page. The <a href="/en/crm/kundendaten-verwalten"><strong>Managing customer data</strong></a> page of the manual that describes the settings in the <strong>Customers » Edit customers</strong> and <strong>System » Customers</strong> menus will be simultaneously available. Once the new <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong> menu has completely replaced the old <strong>Customers » Edit customers</strong> menu, the <strong>Customers » Edit customers</strong> menu as well as the <strong>Managing customer data</strong> page of the manual will be removed.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong> to create data records about contacts and save all relevant information there. You can also edit and delete your contacts in this menu as well as display the addresses, orders, tickets and notes of your contacts, add new addresses, orders, tickets notes and delete existing addresses, tickets and notes. Furthermore, it is possible to take a look at the history of a contact. The history displays, for example, the registration date and if it is a regular account or a guest account.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Notes about detail view, context menu, card view and table view</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you click on a contact in order to display or edit it, the detail view of the contact will open. Via the context menu in the left section of the contact, you can access views such as <strong>Addresses</strong> or <strong>New address</strong>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>By clicking on <strong>Addresses</strong> for example, all addresses that are saved for the contact will be initially displayed as cards. By clicking on <strong>Switch to table view</strong>, the addresses will be displayed in a table. From this view, you can switch back by clicking on <strong>Switch to card view</strong>. Your plentymarkets system will recognise which of the two views you selected. When opening the context menu <strong>Addresses</strong> the next time, the view that was selected last will be displayed.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>When more than one view of the contact is open, a triangle will appear in the view above. Click on the triangle to quickly and easily switch between the open views. Click on the cross to close the contact and remove it from the list.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can get back to the overview of contacts found via the <strong>Overview</strong> view. From this view, you can open as many further contacts as you like. When more than one contact is open, a triangle will appear in the view of the contact that is currently open. Click on the triangle to quickly and easily access contacts that have been opened at least once. Click on the cross to close the contact and remove it from the list.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Creating a contact</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to create a new contact. Add contact options such as email addresses, telephone numbers and, if required, the VAT number. You can also create a new contact, for example, while taking an order over the phone or while filling out a written order. It is also possible to save the contact details of interested parties here. When creating a contact, the system will automatically assign an ID. This ID cannot be changed.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a contact:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Create new contact</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as desired in the <strong>New contact</strong> section. Pay attention to the information given in table 1.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Contact options</strong> section, select the type and sub-type from the drop-down menu and enter the value. Pay attention to the information given in table 1.<br>
→ Click on <strong>Add contact option</strong> to add further contact options.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The contact will be added.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all spread">
<caption class="title">Table 1. Creating a contact</caption>
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 50%;">
<col style="width: 50%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Setting</th>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Explanation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top" colspan="2"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>New contact</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Form of address</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the option from the drop-down menu. This selection is optional.<br>
<strong>Ms.</strong> = Female form of address<br>
<strong>Mr.</strong> = Male form of address</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Title</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter the title of the contact, if required.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>First name</strong>, <strong>Last name</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter the first and last name of the contact.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Client (store)</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the client (store) from the drop-down menu in order to assign the contact to this client (store).<br>
Only those clients will be displayed that have a name entered for them in the store’s <strong>basic settings</strong> under <strong>System » Client</strong>.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Language</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the language for the contact. For example, invoice documents will be sent in this language if you created a template in this language.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Type</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the type. The types <strong>Customer</strong>, <strong>Sales representative</strong>, <strong>Supplier</strong>, <strong>Partner</strong>, <strong>Manufacturer</strong> and <strong>Interested party</strong> can be selected by default. Create further types in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-customer-data#300"><strong>System » Customers » Types</strong></a> menu.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Class</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the class. Classes serve as an internal distinction between customers and which discount will be granted this class, for example. Go to <a href="/en/crm/managing-customer-data#100"><strong>System » Customers » Classes</strong></a> to create further classes. If you want to offer different prices to end customers and sellers in the online store, then this can be done with the <strong>Display of the prices in the online store</strong> option in the configuration of the classes. For end customers (B2C), the gross prices are displayed in the online store. For sellers (B2B), the net prices are displayed in the online store.<br>
Empty option = No assignment to a class<br>
<strong><em>Important:</em></strong> If there is no assignment to a class, the contact will be automatically assigned to the class with the lowest position. As the price display in the online store is configured for each class, check this option for the class with the position 1 so that the correct price is displayed during automatic assignments.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Feedback</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Give feedback about the contact for internal use. Select five red stars for the worst and five yellow stars for the best rating.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Customer number</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter a customer number for the contact. It is a good idea to plan how you want your contacts to be numbered, e.g. consecutively. Customer numbers are not assigned automatically.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Owner</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the owner for the contact. If you do not want to select an owner, select the empty option.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Date of birth</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter the date of birth of the contact in the format yyyy-mm-dd or select it from the calendar.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Newsletter</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Displays if the contact receives the newsletter. It is not possible to manually activate this option. In order to exclude the contact from receiving the newsletter, click on <strong>Delete newsletter</strong>.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Blocked</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select whether or not the contact should be blocked for the specific client (store).<br>
If the option is activated, the contact will be blocked and can no longer log into the online store. If the option is deactivated, the contact will be able to log into the online store.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top" colspan="2"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Contact options</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Type</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the type, e.g. email, telephone or website from the drop-down menu.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Sub-type</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select a sub-type, e.g. work, private or contact person from the drop-down menu.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Value</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter the value.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="200">2. Searching for a contact</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Filter</strong> view, you can search for contacts according to specific criteria. The contacts found will be listed in the <strong>Overview</strong> view. The overview currently displays the following information: ID, company, first name, last name, email address, telephone number, number of orders, postcode and country. How you edit contact data is described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#300"><strong>Editing a contact</strong></a> chapter.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to search for specific contacts, enter a search term in the search fields or select the appropriate drop-down menu settings. You can enter multiple search terms into the search fields at one time. This makes your search run quicker and be more accurate.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Searching for a contact:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Filter</strong> view, enter the search term in the search field or set the filter options in the drop-down menus. Pay attention to the information given in table 2.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Search</strong>.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact will open. As an alternative, open the context menu with a right click to directly access the views of the contact.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all spread">
<caption class="title">Table 2. Filters for contacts</caption>
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 50%;">
<col style="width: 50%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Setting</th>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Explanation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Search</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Click on <strong>Search</strong> without selecting any filter settings. This will display all contacts. Alternatively, limit the search results by using filters and click on <strong>Search</strong>. The contacts found will be listed in the overview.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Reset</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Resets the filter criteria that was entered.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>ID</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Each contact automatically receives a consecutive and unique ID. It doesn’t matter if the data record was saved manually or automatically. Two contacts never have the same ID. The ID is always a real number. "00521" or "ADF8354" e.g. are invalid.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Name</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter the first name and/or last name or the name of the company to search for the contact with this name or company name. The search is also carried out for names and company names that are saved in the address data records of the contact. It is also possible to search only for parts of the name or company name.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Address</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter the name of the street and/or the postcode that is saved for the contact. It is also possible to search only for parts of the street and parts of the house number.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Postcode</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter the postcode that is saved for the contact. The search is also carried out for postcodes that are saved in the address data records of the contact. It is also possible to search only for parts of the postcode.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Town</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter the town that is saved for the contact. The search is also carried out for towns that are saved in the address data records of the contact. It is also possible to search only for parts of the town.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Email</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter the email address to search for the contact with this email address. It is also possible to search only for parts of the email address.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Country</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select a country to only display contacts from this country. The country is saved within the contact data.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Owner</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the owner to only search for contacts with this owner. The owner must be saved in the contact data record.<br>
<strong><em>Important:</em></strong> You can only select users from the drop-down menu who are activated for the <strong>Customer</strong> option in the <strong>Owner</strong> tab of their user account.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Type</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the type to only search for contacts with this type.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Client (store)</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select a client (store) to only display contacts that correspond to this client. The client (store) is saved within the contact data.<br>
<strong><em>Important:</em></strong> Variable users can only select those clients (stores) that they have a right to access. Variable users are given rights within the <a href="/en/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/manage-users#90"><strong>Right</strong></a> tab in the <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong> menu.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Referrer</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the referrer to only search for contacts with this referrer.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="300">3. Editing a contact</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Search the contact by means of the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200"><strong>filter settings</strong></a>. Open the contact by clicking in the line of the contact to edit the contact’s data such as the language, class, date of birth, telephone number and email address, for example. You will find explanations of the settings and options in the sections <strong>Contact</strong> and <strong>Contact options</strong> in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#100"><strong>Creating a contact</strong></a> chapter. Click on <strong>Delete contact option</strong> to delete the contact options.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing a contact:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200"><strong>Searching for a contact</strong></a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the changes as desired. Pay attention to the information given in table 1 in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#100"><strong>Creating a contact</strong></a> chapter.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="400">4. Deleting a contact</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can delete individual contacts. All addresses that are assigned to the contact will be deleted if they are not linked to an order.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting a contact:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200"><strong>Searching for a contact</strong></a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete contact</strong> in the context menu or click on <strong>Delete</strong> above the detail view.<br>
→ A window will open and you need to confirm your decision.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete</strong>.<br>
→ The contact will be deleted and removed from the overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="500">5. Displaying the history</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Each data record contains the history of a contact. The history includes e.g. how long the contact has been registered and when he or she has been logged into your online store for the last time and when the last order was generated. This data will be automatically updated and cannot be changed.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Displaying the history:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200"><strong>Searching for a contact</strong></a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact will open and the history will be displayed in the right section below the <strong>contact options</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Pay attention to the information about the history given in table 3.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
