</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="600">6. Adding an address</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can add as many addresses and as address options as you like. Address options are for example, the VAT number or the telephone number of the contact.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding an address:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200"><strong>Searching for a contact</strong></a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>New address</strong> in the context menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings in the <strong>New address</strong> section. Pay attention to the information given in table 4.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Address options</strong> section, select the type from the drop-down menu and enter the value. Pay attention to the information given in table 4.<br>
→ By clicking on <strong>Add address option</strong>, you can add further address options.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The address will be added to the overview in the <strong>Addresses</strong> section.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
