</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="700">7. Displaying addresses</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>From the open contact, you can display all addresses that are saved for the contact. Besides the ID, company name, first and last name as well as address and country, you can see the address type – invoice address or delivery address – and whether the address is a primary address or not.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If multiple addresses are open, the IDs of the addresses will also be dipslayed in the drop-down menu of the open address data records.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Initially, the addresses of your contact are displayed in card view. By clicking on <strong>Switch to table view</strong>, the addresses will be displayed in a table. Your plentymarkets system will recognise which of the two views you selected. When opening the context menu <strong>Addresses</strong> the next time, the view that was selected last will be displayed.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Up to 25 address data records saved for the contact are displayed per page. If more than 25 addresses are saved for the contact, you can use the toolbar to browse between the pages, select a certain page and to change the number of address data records per page to 50, 75 or 100. Your plentymarkets system will recognise the number of address data records you selected per page. When opening the context menu <strong>Addresses</strong> the next time, the view that was selected last will be displayed.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Displaying addresses:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200"><strong>Searching for a contact</strong></a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Addresses</strong> in the context menu.<br>
→ All addresses that are saved for the contact will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Edit</strong> in order to open the detail view of the address.<br>
→ If you selected the table view, click in the line of the address in order to open the detail view.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="800">8. Editing an address</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can edit addresses as well as address options at any time. Pay attention to the information given in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#600"><strong>Adding an address</strong></a> chapter. Click on <strong>Delete address option</strong> to delete the address options.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing an address:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200"><strong>Searching for a contact</strong></a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Addresses</strong> in the context menu.<br>
→ All addresses that are saved for the contact will initially be displayed as cards.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Edit</strong> in the address card that you want to edit.<br>
→ The detail view of the address will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the changes as desired. Pay attention to the information given in table 4 in the <a href="/en/crm/kontakte-verwalten#700"><strong>Adding an address</strong></a> chapter as well as to the information about the toolbar given in table 5.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
